02/06/2008
TIRANA, Albania -- Police and interior ministry officials visited three southern coastal cities on Saturday (May 31st) to ensure a high level of security for holiday-makers this summer. Deputy Interior Minister Gent Strazimiri and Director-General of the State Police Ahmet Prenci visited Saranda, Vlora and Divjaka. Prenci asked for a detailed inspection of the coastal area, which bans any commercial use of motorboats. (Gazeta Shqipare - 01/06/08; BalkanWeb, TopChannel - 31/05/08)
